I assume modeling/simulation is going to be CAD and such, so I don't think that will be very relevant.
I would go for 227B/C over the Industrial Engineering department stuff, just because these classes are probably going to focus more on software applications than the other department's offerings.

I heard some good things about 110, but I feel like the material is very foundational and not as directly applicable.

Afaik I don't think 113 is useful at all.

I think EE120 is probably the class to take over 118., but it's supposed to be a very foundational class where you the most out of it if you take more classes that build off of it.

No idea about 128A

267 sounds the most directly applicable, especially as a backend engineer for cloud platforms or things like that.

Anyway this are mostly hearsay, I haven't taken any of the courses you listed so seek more opinions
